
Monitor bitrate for a given pid

Usage: tsp -P bitrate_monitor [options] pid

PID:
      Specifies the PID to monitor.

Options:

  -a command
  --alarm-command command
      Command to be run when an alarm is detected (bitrate out of range).

  --min value
      Set minimum allowed value for bitrate (bits/s).
      Default: 10 b/s.

  --max value
      Set maximum allowed value for bitrate (bits/s).
      Default: 4,294,967,295 b/s.

  -p value
  --periodic-bitrate value
      Always report bitrate at the specific interval in seconds, even if the
      bitrate is in range.

  -t value
  --time-interval value
      Time interval (in seconds) used to compute the bitrate.
      Default: 5 s.

  --help
      Display this help text.

  --version
      Display the version number.

